<dl id="n41039e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41039e">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41039e"> 39(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> to sue for / torts <small>Blue</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n41039e"> <li>FW unlocated</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">A wife can only <mark>sue her husband for torts</mark> (i.e., civil wrongs not arising from contract) in connection with the protection and security of her separate property. <small> Maud I. Crofts, <a name="MICW" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#MICW"><cite title="source">Women under English Law</cite></a>, 1st ed. (1925) 40</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
